  "title": "Assistant Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><em><strong>Job Description</strong></em></p><p><u><strong>Job Scope:</strong></u></p><p>The person will oversee the M&E projects from engineering design inception to completion, ensuring compliance with building regulations and specifications; and managing manpower and other resources.</p><p>The person will be working with site personnel, and site activities and be highly involved in the following aspects of the business but not limited to the below:</p><p>· Project management, site meeting, and coordination</p><p>· Engineering & technical study, identify variation works and submit accurate cost implications.</p><p>· Able to schedule, supervise and control sub-contractors to carry out their works accurately and timely in accordance with the contract drawings and specifications.</p><p>· Experience in M&E contracts, documentation, and having an established network of vendors, suppliers & contractors will be an advantage.</p><p>· Undertake Adhoc duties as assigned.</p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>· Good knowledge of various types of M&E systems with piping and cables used in factories, especially in Semiconductor factories, Chemical systems</p><p>· Experience in the Semiconductor industry, design/knowledge of general construction M&E works, is an advantage</p><p>· Independent individual with a drive to make things work.</p><p>· Highly communicative and Self-motivated individual.</p><p>· Possess relevant safety and work certificates (BCSS, WAH) is an advantage</p><p>Interested candidates, please send your updated resume in MS Word format including the followings: </p><p>(1) Current & expected salary<br />(2) Reason(S) for leaving<br />(3) Date of availability </p><p><strong>(We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified)</strong></p>",
